insta_description:
*A continuation of the prior post. ***The following three prints are from the Central Coast of California, printed on Japanese Kozo.

Moving to Washington | Prints for Sale

Over the next week or so, I will be posting some images of finalized pieces, as well as individual prints. I'm heading up to the Olympic Peninsula this coming Spring. An exciting new chapter with many adventures to come. New photographic studies and memories to be made.

I would like to give these pieces a new home prior to, perhaps someone will appreciate them or know others who will. Christmas is right around the corner! I will admit...i despise taking photos of prints. I'm horrible at it and it does no justice to the experience in person...please keep in mind while viewing these on a screen. I'm happy to make others upon request, but consolidating for the move is my goal.

Thank you for the continual support, looking forward to sharing more soon. Happy holidays from the coast! ***The following three prints are from the Central Coast of California, printed on Japanese Kozo.

4x5in print signed and editioned. Happy to ship with or without the frame.

Sincerely,
David King Rowe Iv

**Update: Washington | Unforeseen Circumstances

Hey guys, just finished moving everything into the new place on the Washington Peninsula after driving up from California. These last three weeks have been beautiful. Unfortunately, i've been put in a bit of a tough spot and have to move everything out by the end of the month. Extremely frustrating, but such is the circumstance. I have my truck, photo gear, and belongings with me, including a flatbed film scanner and injet printer. I'm currently reaching out to anyone who might have any connections in the Seattle area, or even the Peninsula here. I would love to stay in WA as i'm up here...and the berries will start to pop up EVERYWHERE...ha. I am happy to provide printing or scanning services for someone if needed. I have my film and digi gear with me as well if anyone needs assistant on shoots. I'm open to any ideas and recommendations be it temporary or long term. I also will consider other states if it is conducive. C'est la vie... Much love,

David King Rowe Iv

insta_description:
Update: Eastern Sierras - Mt. Whitney Valley | Prints
Good morning good morning,

I've been holding onto this piece for some time now, letting it simmer within until this past week. I typically don't enjoy large(r) prints, focusing primarily on shape and form, allowing subject matter to speak volumes over detail and peripheral clutter. This particular scene is an exception. Tucked within a valley below Mt. Whitney, this creature was so glorious in person, pre front storm conditions formed luminous and shimmering clouds above in the distance just over the peaks, quite a special moment witnessed in person. *10.5x16.5in fiber print on Japanese bamboo
*Edition 2 of 25, signed.

I'm happy to print a bit larger on this one as well if anyone desires.

Spring is finally settling in (crossing fingers and eyes) here on the Peninsula. Many trails are still inaccessible due to snow pack, but plenty to explore in the meanwhile. More sunshine and prints to come soon.

All the best,
David King Rowe Iv

insta_description:
Song of Silence | Brutal Reminders
Every so often i find myself humbled by the sheer power of Nature. I spent the day trekking up to a lake for an overnight with the cameras, unsure of how much snow still covered the surrounding valley and water. An eerie silence accompanied me the entire time. Lion tracks scattered the snow every so often, snow covered bends offered up the unknown around every corner. There was but one dry spot under a large tree to provide shelter for a tent through the night. Pitter patter of rain and snow made for a cold but reflective evening. Reminders of how minuscule man is outside his comforts.

Film to be developed soon. A few snapshots until then.

www.DKR4.com

Best.
David King Rowe Iv

I was able to spend two nights up on a very special piece of land, lone oak guardians scattered along winding saltwater kissed  hillsides, overlooking the vast Pacific from high and afar. Fog, rain, hail, then a glorious sunset to reward the treachery. Lots of updates coming soon, 2020 has many new ventures in store. 
Stay tuned, and as always...much love to all those who continue to support this photographic venture.

Sincerely,
David

www.DKR4.com
location.name: Central Coast, Ca

insta_description:
Mid storm, this scene was quite special. Massive yet delicate fluff balls flying over the horizon along the air stream. It's always a joy attempting to frame up and time their arrival just right, harmonizing minimalistic composition with chaotic light and dynamic structures, an ever shifting puzzle...the greatest joy of working in the field.

120 negs are all developed, now onto the 35mm rolls.
